My opinion on geoengineering: some ideas I like (e.g. planting trees) and others I strongly oppose (e.g. SAI and iron fertilization - see LOHAFEX).

You mean like persistent contrails do?

" they create a haze that spreads out like a particulate being fanned out by the jet stream."

Persistent contrails spread into sheets of cirrus via wind shear.  You somewhat seem to understand this, so why the attachment to a 'chemtrail' fairy tale when persistent contrails are already known and understood?  

"People have collected the metallic particles in controlled studies and found they contained extremely high amounts of fine barium and aluminum oxide particles along with other polymers."

Link, and citations, please.  Make sure you include the process and collection methodology, and how the findings correlate to known 'chemtrailing' operations, along with how other natural or anthropogenic sources of said findings were eliminated.

textOriginal:
@PKydland "IF it has always been condensation from the high bypass turbo fan jet engines, why do some aircraft leave a trail and others don‚Äôt?"
Because the environmental parameters differ. How do you explain that some days you have a clear blue sky and on other days clouds cover the whole sky?
"Wouldn‚Äôt all engines ( since all commercial airliners have the same ) create condensation at the altitude that commercial airliners operate?"
No. If the humidity is low and/or the temperature is too high you won't see a contrail.
Here is a description of an experiment you can conduct at home. Take a glass and put it into the freezer for an hour. Remove it after the period and see what is happening. The water dontained in the surrounding air will condense on the surface of the glass. It will take quite some time until the water disappears.
Now take the same glass on a warm sunny day and put it outside for an hour. After that period bring it back inside. No water will condense on the surface of the glass.
What did you prove? You proved that the same glass behaves different in different environmental conditions. The same physics applies to contrails. The inside of your home can be seen as the hot jet engine exhaust gas whereas the warm or cold glass represents the dust particle in the surrounding air.
I hope that I did not make it too complicate and you can understand that experiment.

textOriginal:
Stahlah Yes, contrails are a normal thing behind airplanes.  There are plenty of photographs as far back as World War 2.  Water is a product of combustion.  My aircraft goes through 5200 lbs of fuel per hour at cruise, and almost double that while it climbs to cruise.  A 747, when the airlines flew them, would go through over 300,000 pounds of fuel on international flights.  This is just one link that can explain what you see.

https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-018-04068-0

Chemicals in jet exhaust (and would be present in a contrail).  Yes.  Kerosene is a hydrocarbon.  Products of combustion would be H2O, and various NOx compounds, as well as CO, SOx, and CO2.  Jet fuels contain biocide chemicals to prevent bacterial growth (it forms a rubbery byproduct that can clog fuel filters and injectors), ice preventers (prevents ice crystals from forming in the fuel that can clog filters).

There are also trace amounts of a number of metals.  Here is an article with a table so you can see that.

https://apps.dtic.mil/dtic/tr/fulltext/u2/a396143.pdf

In Jet A, there was No Detectable aluminum.  There was 3 parts per billion Ba, and 12 parts per billion Sr.  So let‚Äôs break that down for people with no math skills (like yourself).  
An Airbus A320, at cruise, is burning around 5200 lbs per hour, or about 86 pounds per minute.  In one minute, the Jet travels 8 nautical miles, or 9.2 statute miles.  That is .0000004587 ounces of Barium in one minute of contrail.  That is .0000129996 grams.  A grain of salt (wiki) is .03 cm on a side.  It‚Äôs volume is .000027 cm cubed.  The density of sodium chloride is 2.16 grams per cm cubed.  

Barium and Sodium are two different elements, but I am trying to form a mental picture of the amount of trace Ba that would be in a 9 mile long contrail.  With the math above, there is approximately the equivalent of 1/5 of a grain of salt volume in a 9 mile long contrail.  

So, are you going to claim something smaller than a grain of salt can be made into a particulate trail that is 9 miles long.  THIS IS PRECISELY WHY YOU SHOULD UNDERSTAND SCIENCE before speaking on it.

videoTitle: Why Jets Leave White Trails In The Sky

videoTitle: Why Jets Leave White Trails In The Sky
textOriginal: Nick Nikovski is correct. Those weren't wingtip vortices or actual condensation trails ("contrails"). It was smoke from canisters fitted on the wingtips for air display purposes, which make impressive trails through the sky & help spectators on the ground keep sight of the aircraft. The pilot switches them on & off. It's a common feature at all airshows & can even be done in a range of colours. Red, white & blue are the patriotic favourites.

videoTitle: Why Jets Leave White Trails In The Sky
textOriginal:
Mike Schwartz When the plane flies through the air, it pushes air molecules out of the way. So, just behind the wings there is an area of lower pressure, as air has been pushed out of the way. So, the condensation from the engines is pulled along with the air, and the air travels towards the tips of the wings, as there is a pressure difference there. I don't think I explained the
At very well, but I hope you understand :)

textOriginal: As a nuclear professional, I do a lot of consideration of the effects of radiation. I think this was a pretty good, nuanced view. What may be interesting would be to separate the skin cancers from the rest. One very well may see that internal cancers actually were lower (this is actually a very common result in radiated populations). Given the window area in the cockpit, I would not be surprised to see skin cancer from UV (not entirely blocked by windows) vs. Ionizing radiation from the Cosmos. I believe the same is seen in truckers, even if they don't keep their arm out the window.

videoTitle: How much Radiation do Pilots get from space?
textOriginal: It probably is the UV especially when you consider that at altitude the proportion that would be in the form of UVB is likely to be higher, normally 90% of that is absorbed before reaching ground level but by moving up above the significant majority of the atmosphere that absorption would decrease substantially. Since UVB is more energetic than UVA that could make a significant difference, still not as bad as UVC but the atmosphere is so close to being completely opaque to UVC that it doesn't penetrate that far and probably still doesn't really apply much to commercial flight levels. Mostly going to have a bigger impact on increasing the exposure to UVB and to a lesser extent UVA as the transparency rapidly becomes less transparent as you move above violet and into the UVA and UVB range since that is basically the upper threshold of the visible window.

videoTitle: How much Radiation do Pilots get from space?
textOriginal:
There is data showing that flight crews suffer higher than average levels of skin cancer compared to average population. This is undoubtably due to UV exposure, possibly aided by all those JET-A fumes and other chemical fumes around aircraft (my own hypothesis).

The relationships between accumulated dose, dose rate and risk is a highly controversial subject in science and politics. 
The cosmic background radiation to pilots, flight crew and passengers is not causing 250'000 - 500'000 premature deaths per year as predicted by the current dose risk models used in the nuclear industry and radiation protection fields. For the chronic exposure prevalent at high altitude flying I would be inclined to say that the risk threashold is somewhere between 400 - 800 mGy/year according to the data published from the BEIR VII reports (Hiroshima and Nagasaki survivors). Though the biological mechnisms of hormesis are compelling I am not willing to stretch my neck as far as to say that exposures between 50-100 mGy/year would be beneficial but I would like to see more data on that particular subject...

textOriginal:
"One very well may see that internal cancers actually were lower (this is actually a very common result in radiated populations)"
Can confirm that as a biologist. As I stated in my other post, the most popular hypothesis is that the increased DNA damage actually triggers DNA repair mechanisms and makes them work. The DNA damage is a signal for DNA repair mechanisms and more damage means those systems become more active and more transcribed (produced) by the cell and there will be more of them. Up to a certain point, when they get saturated and cannot keep up with the new damage. You can often see slight decrease of cancer in people exposed to slightly above normal radiation levels. (does not work much for Japanese). At a higher doses the cancer count suddenly jumps up.

textOriginal: Very nice overview of the subject, well done! Two remarks worth mentioning: A lot of the high energy cosmic radiation is protons, and this kind of radiation doesn't occur naturally, little is known about long term health effects. Protons tend to go deep into the body and decay in a number of secondary radioactive particles there. Second remark is Solar Flares (Coronal mass ejections from the Sun). The particle flow from these is astronomical and very dangerous.They can be predicted with a couple of days warming, and you should avoid to fly near them if at all possible. They can even knock out power lines on ground.

videoTitle: How much Radiation do Pilots get from space?
textOriginal: RR lease engines to some airlines complete with maintenance. That's one of the reasons MH370 could be monitored a little after it went off radar - the engine telemetry was still being monitored by Rolls Royce in Derby England. Unfortunately the data can only tell you throttle setting, fuel flow, temperatures of various sections, vibration and noise levels and such like. I could be wrong but the thrust thing is for example buying 10 billion pound seconds. For a Trent 1000 that would be 200,000 seconds at cruise throttle (if I remember correctly 50,000 pounds thrust). On a four engine aircraft that would be only 50,000 seconds, or about 14 hours flight. Then you have all the malarkey of take-off thrust (which is on some engines rated as more than maximum thrust) and landing thrust (the engines can be almost at idle at points). It can be calculated but would be a pain in the neck without a computer monitoring second by second.

textOriginal: @Buddy Unfair? This man is a career criminal. Very unlikely he would ever be able to function normally in society without falling back to his old ways. You know, getting your house burglarized/having the things you worked hard for taken is a very traumatic experience. I've experienced this myself. I'm pretty sure his victims are glad this man will be locked away for some time to come.  Don't get me wrong. I'm no one to judge. We all make mistakes in life.  However,  society has laws in place for a reason. If you don't abide by them there are consequences.

LIFE ISNT EASY .... I don't want to force anything on yall but man I've had so many problems and the only true way to come out of them victorious is thru the Lord God Almighty... I know society makes everyone think being religious is for deluded people but please open your eyes it's not..¬† I plead to yall just say a prayer to God commit all your worries fears, regrets and deepest problems into his hands.. read the bible and keep praying to him in Jesus Name .. I promise you your life will change for the better I promise you

I was pondering on suicide, I wanted to run away from home but I prayed to the Lord God and all of a sudden ..things started moving forward in my life.. I've done so many evil things in my past.. things that i think any other person would kill me for if they were God but God kept me alive and well

Believe that Jesus died on the cross for all of our sins to be forgiven and to give us eternal life in heaven
You may think I'm crazy but I'm begging just try this read the bible pray and watch yourself rise to heights you never expected 

Dont fall into the tricks of the world I'm begging

I apologise for this being too long

Imma try and send this out to loads of comments sections.. I hope this touched your soul.. if it did please like the message and comment¬† let's make it together km

videoTitle: Inside the Mind of a Thief | Burglar Confessions
textOriginal:
@Ren Allen I felt the same when I lost a good job because a Manager would authorise work holidays; so would arrange cover for me - so I thought!  I would come into work, from holiday to a list of complaints; people didn't even show up to cover me as agreed; people came did a few unhelpful things, missed out the crucial things, then left doing quarter not even  half a job! The contract client wasnt happy, I would come in off holiday to a list of complaints......those doing the complaining are the contract Bosses! 

I had a quiet word with my Boss, and he promised to nail it next time! So I  had a holiday again, guess what? Same problems again, then the contract was being taken on by someone new; by now everything was being pinned on a new start; by now the contract Bosses 'hated' my Boss, and I was seen as part of the Bosses company; so I was out of there. The company taking over were foreign and paid alot lower than the company I was with now; and I knew the new company....had wage issues with them before found them really really uncaring when wages are wrong

I was out, I was at home; the fact the Manager kept his job yet, I lost mine put me in a state of depression. I couldn't even contact the Manager to find out my wages situation; as they were not answering my calls....I said to Jesus VIA my mind, not even loud, I spoke by concentrating and speaking to Jesus through loud thoughts; I said " I have had enough, I just want to lie here and gently slip away Jesus." I lay in bed, ready; not to eat or drink, had no knowledge of any money coming through to me anyway due to the Ignorant; arrogant Manager not answering my calls. 

Suddenly, I felt my mind flick a switch in the dark; light shone up ahead, my mind started thinking " get up, get a pen get on the internet look up the office of the company your Manager works for" My mind spoke.....next thing you know the office and me are communicating; I have cheques come through and I have no more 'suicide attempts,' I actually 'thrive' am very much 'alive;' and moved on...

I thank Jesus for this even now, years later. Everyone I urge you to do as Jesuswalks advised; I want to also share with you a 'truth' of another kind.....a 'Doctor' was refused air time, yes a 'Doctor!' Why? Why would all these news stations: BBC CH4 ITV  CNN NBC refuse  a 'Doctors' appearance on air? Well, pull up a chair, make a drink, relax; and watch the entire video, many people speak; it's the 'Doctor' that speaks the most and who I want you to focus on, listen carefully too: Tap into you tube: OMG!! textOriginal:
@Sumboo Casper 
Actually if you pay more attention in the video he says that if no one answers, he is more likely to break into the house!

If you are afraid of coming face to face with a thief, you probably want to follow the advice NOT to open the door BUT ANSWER the stranger anyway, perhaps bluffing by saying that you are calling the owners (or maybe calling them actually).

Rather than telling your customers you don't answer the door, maybe warn them that you don't open / talk to strangers without verifying their identity with the owners.

Explain that it is for the safety of their home so your caution may become a valued trait rather than an irritating thing.

Always keep your mobile charged and close at hand, perhaps with quick keys to call the owners / a trusted person / the police (a call can save your life).

Finally, consider getting yourself a pepper spray (easy to carry and easy to use). Maybe it can give you some peace of mind.

Stay safe.

textOriginal: @Jesus Walks amen brother, you definitely just helped me. Ive been struggling and battling with myself so hard latley. The pressure and stress is getting to the point where im almost broken again, while satan is standing there smiling. I did something I havent done in a long time a couple days ago. I closed my eyes, with  such pain in my heart, tears running down my face, quite literally losing my will to live , and prayed to God whole heartedly to guide me again. To please help me have strength when satan is close and I am weak and vulnerable. That I am so sorry for knowing whats right and just, and still choosing to do wrong and evil. Then moment after I said I pray this in the name of Jesus Christ, I was overcome with conviction and the holy spirit,  literally felt chills throughout my body. So Istarted to pray and repent. The next day came and when I woke up I felt great! I hopped out of bed thanking God and started making a to do list for the day. Then moments later, I completely fell face first back into the same stuff that had me searching so desperately for the lord and nearly a shell of a man, and immediately felt hopeless. That was yesterday. Since then ive still felt like dirt, untill I came accross ur comment. 2 major but subtle things stood out to me the most among you're amazing story. READ YOUR BIBLE, and PRAY TO THE LORD. Huge brother!! So huge!!! Yesterday when I woke up I did neither. After writing this comment, and tomorrow and so on, I will make a consious and willing effort to tead my bible and pray every day.  Thank you so much man, youre story is very inspiring and has definitely shed light in a dark place. Thank you, and God bless üòÅ

LIFE ISNT EASY .... I don't want to force anything on yall but man I've had so many problems and the only true way to come out of them victorious is thru the Lord God Almighty... I know society makes everyone think being religious is for deluded people but please open your eyes it's not..¬† I plead to yall just say a prayer to God commit all your worries fears, regrets and deepest problems into his hands.. read the bible and keep praying to him in Jesus Name .. I promise you your life will change for the better I promise you

I dont want to be seen as the deluded guy in the comment section but I'm literally pouring my heart out

I thought my sins were too bad and that I will never succeed in my dreams.. but I forgot that in John 3:16 it says "For God so love the world that he gave his only begotten son that whosoever believes in him shall not perish but have everlasting life"

Believe that Jesus died on the cross for all of our sins to be forgiven and to give us eternal life in heaven
You may think I'm crazy but I'm begging just try this read the bible pray and watch yourself rise to heights you never expected 

Dont fall into the tricks of the world I'm begging

I apologise for this being too long

Imma try and send this out to loads of comments sections.. I hope this touched your soul.. if it did please like the message and comment¬† let's make it together

videoTitle: Inside the Mind of a Thief | Burglar Confessions
textOriginal: I used to steal from houses when i was 12, the cops took an interest in me and even called me in an office at school.  The detective was actually a nice guy, when he saw how scared i was he looked kind of embarrassed actually.  Then I stole a bb gun from a Builders emporium and one of my friends told his asshole friend and somehow my dad found out about it.  He paid for the gun, made me apologize, then took me home and beat me with a piece of wood for a while.  Between the living in fear for months, to the beatings from my dad,  my criminal career did not last too long after that.   I would rather do practically anything than keep doing that kind of behavior, and just waiting for the cops to come and get you to go to prison.  Especially now - surveillance of ALL kinds - cameras, motion sensors, lasers, facial recognition, and I'm absolutely certain they already have, or soon will have some sort of device to read your mind, never doubt it.  Such anti-theft measures are damn near omnipotent in most places, when I did this shit it was the early 1970's when they had nothing like they have now.

God is holy. No sin will ever enter his presence, for ‚Äúrighteousness and justice are the foundation of his throne‚Äù (Psalm 97:2).

Humanity is sinful. ‚ÄúFor all have sinned and fall short of the glory of God‚Äù (Romans 3:23). 
 
Sin separates all people from God. ‚ÄúYour iniquities have made a separation between you and your God, and your sins have hidden his face from you‚Äù (Isaiah 59:2). 

It is impossible for humans to save themselves. ‚ÄúBy works of the law no human being will be justified in his sight‚Äù (Romans 3:20). 

CAN I BE SAVED?

God sent his Son to be your Savior. ‚ÄúIn this is love, not that we have loved God but that he loved us and sent his Son to be the propitiation for our sins‚Äù (1 John 4:10). 

The living Savior invites sinners to receive him ‚ÄúCome to me, all who labor and are heavy laden, and I will give you rest‚Äù (Matthew 11:28) 

Forgiveness of sins and salvation can be yours today. ‚Äú For Christ also suffered once for sins, the righteous for the unrighteous, that he might bring us to God‚Äù (1 Peter 3:18). 

HOW CAN I BE SAVED?

Agree with God that you are a lost sinner unable to save yourself. ‚ÄúGod shows his love for us in that while we were still sinners, Christ died for us.‚Äù (Romans 5:8) 

Believe that Jesus Christ died for your sins and ask him to be your Savior. ‚ÄúTo all who did receive him, who believed in his name, he gave the right to become children of God‚Äù (John 1:12). 

Confess the Lord Jesus Christ. ‚ÄúIf you confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved (Romans 10:9) 

‚ÄúTruly truly, I say to you, whoever hears my word and believes him who sent me has eternal life. He does not come into judgment, but has passed from death to life‚Äù( John 5:24).

@Nico Ya...nothing to be proud of.I look back on those times and I regret it.I no longer looked at cars as objects of transport and the means for people to get to work to make a living to feed their families.I looked at them as cash ...partying to sustain certain lifestyle.Today I am 37 and look at thos 10 years of my life a failure.I am ashamed.From my town to a few other towns and cities I am known as a car thief.There are times when I walk with my head down.It took ALONG time to realize this but I consider myself lucky to have done so.I have a new family and its them now what is important.Not selfish Mike.Sorry for the long ass response.
Merry Christmas to you and your family!

videoTitle: Inside the Mind of a Thief | Burglar Confessions
textOriginal:
@Charlie Brown I mean I kinds disagree.I mean for me it was cars and its not break a window and touch some wires and off you go.Its more technical than that.Different makes and models have different ways of opening them and starting them.
Like say a 2001 honda civic you need to change the computer and the switch with the coded key..a 2004 Gm you need to do all that and change the speedometer then wait for a reset be t you can start it.It may not be a trade but you need to learn it.And once you know how to start pretty much anything than you can call yourself a professional. We don't have felonies here in Canada and the sentences are A HELL OF A LOT LESS as well.I had 72 charges and got 3 years.In the US I would probably still be in prison.

There is no such thing as a 'professional' criminal. Crime isn't an occupation or a skill/trade u go to school for. There are no health benefits or retirement plan/401k...... 'criminal' aint professional till u can find it in the phone book.... However, one can always conduct oneself with the utmost professionalism while pursuing a life a crime. 

Just 2 cents from a 10 time felony convicted life long career criminalüòâ

textOriginal: @Lil They can grow in just about any soil type and the U.S. Department of Agriculture Hardiness zones 6 to 9 is best. Eastern North Carolina is 7b to 8a zones so they should grow fine. Are you over watering, or under? About 10-15 liters per plant are necessary once or twice a week when they are young new plantings, this includes rainfall. The tree is only drought-tolerant after it gets established. Potassium is very important too. Is the ground heavy clay that drains slowly? Did you plant on a slope? They prefer flat ground and somewhat loose soil at the start. If it's highly alkaline dirt that may affect it as well.  Did you mulch around the base and not push against the tree? When did you plant it? Lots of reasons a plant might not survive the first year.

@Mr. Hallman Contrails are thin and disappear rapidly when the atmosphere is not too cold (above minus 40 Celsius) and not very damp. In humid and cold air (around minus 60 Celsius) they linger, up to a few hours. As they stay , they can "cross the sky", they superimpose with previous contrails leaved by other planes. They spread and widen, especially if there is wind shear. When all the planes in the previous hour have leaved persistent contrails, their contrails cover a large part of the sky. When the cold front is coming, the contrails merge with the incoming cirrus, and all together, contrails and cirrus, may cover the whole sky.
Where is your evidence they would be chemtrails ?

Chaff (countermeasure)
Language
Watch
Edit

Modern US Navy RR-144 (top) and RR-129 (bottom) chaff countermeasures and containers. Note how the strips of the RR-129 chaff (bottom) are of different widths, while those of the RR-144 (top) are all the same width. The RR-144 is designed to prevent interference with civil ATC radar systems.
Chaff, originally called Window[1] by the British and D√ºppel by the Second World War era German Luftwaffe (from the Berlin suburb where it was first developed), is a radar countermeasure in which aircraft or other targets spread a cloud of small, thin pieces of aluminium, metallized glass fibre or plastic, which either appears as a cluster of primary targets on radar screens or swamps the screen with multiple returns.

Modern armed forces use chaff (in naval applications, for instance, using short-range SRBOC rockets) to distract radar-guided missiles from their targets. Most military aircraft and warships have chaff dispensing systems for self-defense. An intercontinental ballistic missile may release in its midcourse phase several independent warheads as well as penetration aids such as decoy balloons and chaff.

https://journals.ametsoc.org/doi/pdf/10.1175/1520-0469%281972%29029%3C1367%3AMOTGOT%3E2.0.CO%3B2


The aircraft is a small Sabreliner jet at FL290 in air of -38.2 degrees C. The two engines produced 1.73 grams of water vapour per meter as a result of fuel combusted. A Sabreliner has a maximum payload of 2000lbs. The resultant persistent contrail was measured at 66,000lbs per square kilometre. textOriginal:
@KRIS ZANE 


"keep believing what you believe. Let me believe what I believe."


??? It isn't a question of 'belief'. Weather modification is the legal and technical terminology for cloud seeding which isn't sinister in the slightest and completely transparent and in the public domain. There are many private companies that freely advertise their services and contracts online - you just found one. You loud hire them for an event yourself. Cloud seeding isn't by any means widespread though and actually, the reliability and science behind it is questionable. Furthermore, since silver iodide and not elemental silver typically constitutes the seeding material, the claims of negative environmental impact have been found to be insignificant - the material used for additional nucleation injected into the clouds does not exceed the level of inflow of these chemicals to the atmosphere from natural and anthropogenic sources.


Geoengineering meanwhile is divided into two branches - GGR and SRM. With the exception of ground based albedo modification, the latter is entirely in the province of hypothetical research proposal and computer modelling. 


Both cloud seeding and Geoengineering have nothing to do with each other, and nothing whatsoever to do with the contrails that you are seeing. Neither would actually leave a trail - far less a 100 mile plume in the wake of a jet aircraft. Cloud seeding aims to introduce additional nucleating onto existing cumulus and stratiform masses and so is conducted by light aircraft, usually at altitudes between 2 - 6,000 feet.  SRM, in the form of Stratsospheric Aerosol Injection would aim to reproduce the cooling effect of volcanic aerosols and so would need to be deployed in the mid stratosphere. 65,000-70,000 feet which is double the altitude of the trails that you are seeing. Because it would be designed to release a fine mist of aerosols, even if it was happening, as a ground based observer, you wouldn't even know it was in progress.

textOriginal:
@AnUnapologeticApologist 


"Look up the video from Top Gear you can see NASA generates water vapor that ascends to the sky (looks just as a normal cloud) then one hour later it rained in that same area."


Such viral inaccuracy and idiocy relates to NASA tests of its powerful RS-25 and RS-68 engines at Stennis Space Center in Mississippi. The RS-25 engine powered the Space Shuttle and a similar version will be used for NASA's new Space Launch System. Stennis Space Center in Bay St. Louis, Mississippi has been a longtime test facility for such engines and consequently these tests have generated "fake news" over the years - particularly footage of the Jeremy Clarkson feature which has been dishonestly appropriated and titled...the modus operandi of online conspiracy theorists who dupe their believers and followers through confirmation bias. 


The exhaust from the RS-25 is primarily water vapour because the engine burns liquid hydrogen and liquid oxygen. Not hard to anticipate what happens when they combine, resulting in dihydrogen monoxide...which you may recognise as H20. Therefore, the "clouds" that you see in the pictures or videos are a by-product of a very simple scientific process. If the water vapor condenses, it actually may form drops large enough to fall as liquid or what appears as rain. The original Facebook video is a combined video of the RS-25 engine on the A-1 stand and the RS-68 commercial engine on the B-1 stand at NASA‚Äôs Stennis Space Center in Mississippi.
The Top Gear YouTube clip from 2010 shows the RS-68 commercial test at Stennis.


To reiterate, the engines in the video run on liquid oxygen and liquid hydrogen propellants. The chemical composition of water is H2O (hydrogen and oxygen). These are mixed in the combustion chamber and ignited, which results in extremely high-temperature steam (6000 degree F) coming out of the nozzle at a very high rate and pressure. That steam rises in the atmosphere, creating a steam cloud that cools off and turns back into water and rains depending on the temperature and humidity at the time of the test. There is also water flowing in the flame deflector which also mixes in the cloud. The steam released during a test is water and does not pollute the atmosphere.

The fact that planes fly at higher altitude nowadays, as oppose to 40 years ago, may also be a contributing factor to why contrails persist. As contrails are also moisture in the air, like clouds, they are also affected by these factors. Now as to the idea that we are being sprayed by chemicals. To get a decent coat of pesticide on crops in order to be effective a crop duster needs to fly at dangerously low altitude to avoid having it drifting to a nearby town or adjacent fields. At high altitude any chemicals would be spread so thin that the amount needed to be effective would be enough to carpet the entire sky and thick enough to block out the sun. Firstly chemtrails are an online hoax originally perpetrated in the late 1990s by "shock jocks" such as Art Bell on Cost to Coat AM a commercial station that manufactures conspiracy theory to order to inflate ratings and thus sell more advertising airtime. Moving up into the stratosphere???? It's called Stratospheric Aerosol Injection - it has always been designated for altitudes between 65-70,000ft. Now allow me to educate you...

The purpose of SAI has always been clearly defined. The aim is to simulate the cooling effects of a major volcanic eruption after which large quantities of sulphur dioxide and hydrochloric acid are ejected into the mid stratosphere. Once formed, these aerosols stay in the stratosphere for about two years. They reflect sunlight, reducing the amount of energy reaching the lower atmosphere and the Earth's surface, cooling them. The relative coolness of 1993 is thought to have been a response to the stratospheric aerosol layer that was produced by the Mt. Pinatubo eruption. The relative influence of volcanoes on the Junge layer varies considerably according to the number and size of eruptions in any given time period, and also of quantities of sulphur compounds released. The stratospheric aerosol layer is sustained by natural emissions of carbonyl sulphide (OCS) through biogenic processes. Carbonyl sulphide is relatively stable can mix into the stratosphere where it is photochemically broken down resulting in the formation of microscopic droplets of sulphuric acid. 

Keith has identified a range of possible materials to simulate/catalyse this process. Small scale trials commence this summer involving one KG of material. The objective is beyond that o disperse water, followed by small quantities of calcium carbonate and possibly hydrogen sulphide. Such stratospheric particles exist as thin veils of dust or sulphuric acid droplets at altitudes of 12 to 18 miles.

videoTitle: Fighter Pilot Reveals SHOCKING TRUTH about CHEMTRAILS!
textOriginal:
Hi CW!

Great, concise explanation and refutation. Please allow me to add a clarification and a couple of points:

1. Water Vapor is gaseous, it's invisible. In the cold air behind the aircraft, Water Vapor inside the warm air condenses into liquid water. It almost immediately freezes into ice crystals, which is what is visible from the ground.

2. I've only heard the chemtrails to be used for weather mod, not mind mod. You may "Mover" in other circles, though.

3. Even though the liquid portion of a "chemtrail" might evaporate, the allegation is that the remaining  effective chemicals drift down and expand outward.  The problem with that is, as you partly pointed out:

a. At about 6 lbs/gallon, at least 20 tons of liquid would be required per aircraft to be even slightly effective. Commercial aircraft would only be able to carry a few passengers in addition to this load.

b. If the chems are added to the fuel, it would reduce power produced by the engines, further reducing the payload of the aircraft. 

c. Chems added to fuel would increase wear and reduce the reliability and life of engines.

d. Aircraft stability, handling and safety would be reduced by the weight and slosh-effect of the chems.

e. a-d above would be obvious to anyone tracking airline costs, miles flown, etc.

4. Another allegation is that "we didn't have persistent chemtrails until the government started spraying." What this ignores is that engine design has vastly changed, even from the 70s, when I was involved in Naval Aviation. Nowadays, high-bypass turbofans are mostly in use. These form a "shield" of blown and relatively unheated air in a tube shape around the hot exhaust. This would tend to slow the mixing of ambient air with the  ice crystals in exhaust, increasing the contrails' persistence.

I appreciate your analysis and plan to link this video on a few sites with some die-hard "chemtrail" advocates. If they're not convinced, perhaps some open-minded viewers will be.

Fly safely!

PS Interesting about the ZR-1. I haven't viewed in a while & thought the Camaro was "it" for you. I do  get vicarious pleasure from your purchases. I've had a lot of cars, the fastest either the bi-turbo RX-7 or the Mustang Cobra. I'm now retired & ended up with an FR-S, which handles great but is no speed demon. That's probably for the best, as I stopped getting tickets when I bought it.

You sure about that? 


https://youtu.be/NrTaiyI68z0


Not all aircraft cruise at FL400 - moreover, you are on occasions also observing these trails at half the altitude. 


‚ÄúWho better to fly these things than...NOBODY‚Äù


Pilotless planes are certainly not a technical impossibility. We have the capability. Just as we have the capability to be living in domed colonies on the moon. But because it‚Äôs possible doesn‚Äôt mean that it‚Äôs affordable, practical, safe, or even desirable. And the technological and logistical challenges are to say the least ‚Äì formidable.


It takes the better part of a decade to design, build, and test-fly a conventional commercial plane. Neither Boeing nor Airbus has a new aircraft platform currently under such development, purely in the stages of research. Furthermore, pilotless aircraft would necessitate a vast ‚Äî and currently prohibitively expensive rebuilding of pretty much the entire civil aviation infrastructure, from a totally new air traffic control concept to the redesign of airports. The global cost of this will be enormous.  And that‚Äôs after developing a fleet of tens of thousands of aircraft that are safe and reliable enough for fully autonomous operations. And you‚Äôd still need pilots to operate these aircraft from the ground. 

That said, the long term gains are substantial. Pilotless aircraft may save the industry ¬£35b a year. Another barrier is public perception/resistance to the notion of a fully automated flight deck, but this is so far in the future and even when we get there it is going to take a very brave airline to fully remove personnel from the cockpit.

Absolute rubbish. As I explained, HAARP was scheduled to be deconstructed but although currently under refurbishment, has actually grown in its capabilities due to the continued involvement of over 15 universities that not only played a crucial role in designing its original research specifications and instrumentation but still have involvement in its development. HAARP is powered by five 2500 kilowatt generators being driven by diesel locomotive engines.


"BTW, HAARP was originally a US Navy operation, why would that be if its just an atmospheric research center with over 1 square miles of antenna array?"


Because one of its original designations was to explore the Luxembourg-Gorky effect to enhance long range communications. HAARP has been able to create Extremely Low Frequency waves as low as 1 Hertz, the hydroacoustic potential of this meant that the Navy could more effectively communicate with its fleet of  submarines worldwide - though at an almost uselessly slow data rate.

textOriginal:
It's called cloud seeding, geoengineering, weather warfare. Video: what in the world are they spraying? 
Weathermodification.com

 About Us
The Oxford Geoengineering Programme was founded in 2010 as an initiative of the Oxford Martin School at the University of Oxford.
Geoengineering - the deliberate large-scale intervention in the Earth's natural systems to counteract climate change - is a contentious subject and rightly so.

The Oxford Geoengineering Programme seeks to engage with society about the issues associated with geoengineering and conduct research into some of the proposed techniques. The programme does not advocate implementing geoengineering, but it does advocate conducting research into the social, ethical and technical aspects of geoengineering. This research must be conducted in a transparent and socially informed manner.

What Is Geoengineering?
Simple schematic of various proposed SRM and CDR techniques (Lenton & Vaughn, 2009)
Simple schematic of various proposed SRM and CDR techniques (Lenton & Vaughn, 2009)

Visual representation of proposed geoengineering techniques (New Scientist, 2009)
Visual representation of proposed geoengineering techniques (New Scientist, 2009)

Geoengineering is the deliberate large-scale intervention in the Earth‚Äôs natural systems to counteract climate change.
There is wide range of proposed geoengineering techniques. Generally, these can be grouped into two categories:

Solar Radiation Management (SRM) or Solar Geoengineering
SRM techniques aim to reflect a small proportion of the Sun‚Äôs energy back into space, counteracting the temperature rise caused by increased levels of greenhouse gases in the atmosphere which absorb energy and raise temperatures. Some proposed techniques include:

Albedo enhancement. Increasing the reflectiveness of clouds or the land surface so that more of the Sun‚Äôs heat is reflected back into space.
Space reflectors. Blocking a small proportion of sunlight before it reaches the Earth.
Stratospheric aerosols. Introducing small, reflective particles into the upper atmosphere to reflect some sunlight before it reaches the surface of the Earth
http://www.geoengineering.ox.ac.uk/www.geoengineering.ox.ac.uk/what-is-geoengineering/what-is-geoengineering/index.html

@GManGT Without proper analysis I can't explain those in particular. Likely though, they are just transporting those containers somewhere, or any number of reasons. 
I can however note that the attachments behind the wings or under the plane as depicted are horrible ideas as they affect aerodynamics negatively, and b) you can see them outside the plane, almost certainly with pair of good binoculars. All the avid plane spotters would have noted it was odd. 
And there are planes that disperse chemicals: crop dusters and firefighting planes. Neither is flown at particularly high altitude, and if you see either type over your area dispersing things, you a) live on a farm, b) are in or near an area on fire, or c) have received several public notices that they have to spray for mosquitos due to a disease spreading or far greater than normal numbers (though they prefer trucks not planes so they don't hurt the bees and such). And the stuff from the mosquito spray is just what they put on the scalp to treat lice. Firefighting chemicals from planes are typically reddish, though some also drop water. 
And honestly, if firefighting or insecticide vehicles of any sort are in your area, you have far bigger problems than the chemicals they are releasing. And crop dusters really only are used around farms and such, so they aren't something you'll see dispersing stuff over a city. 

Honestly, I suspect the pictures of apparatus behind the wings/under the plane are doctored. The ones with tanks probably serve a legitimate purpose, and those and others are probably misrepresented as being something other than what they are.
I do think there are conspiracies out there, conspiracies to make people panic and live in fear needlessly and overlook the real problems in this world. People are starving and have unsafe drinking water and they have got you looking at the sky in fear over trails of condensation. If you want to find out what is poisoning us, look at the water and how it is transported often through corroded old pipes, old chemicals in buildings (like asbestos), mold, run-off from old mines and chemical plants, our tendency to use stronger chemicals than are required to clean things around the house, and most people eating food that is empty calories and laden with extra junk we wouldn't have if we made it fresh. And you may want a CO2 and a radon detector too, just because sometimes those come around. 
I am just saying to look at the real and confirmed problems before looking at the unknown suspicions.

Im not saying anything for or against the chemtrails-conspiracy... But just because contrails are water doesn't mean that adding chemicals (for various purposes, weather control, mind control idk) isnt done. It just disproves the incoherent nuts who phrase it as if there would be no trails at all if it weren't for the chemicals... And also, I guess, people who look into the sky, and see a bunch of contrails in all directions, and use that to conclude that the area has been targeted by chemtrails.
It is irrational to conclude that there are chemicals in the contrails, but it doesn't mean that it can't happen. Geo-engineering is a seriously debated science field which includes dumping chemicals/particles from airplanes etc., and lots of places have had chemicals dumped on them from air. For example roundup in forest areas in Norway, just before it became illegal. It was proposed to dump it from helicopters in a lot of places, I am not 100% sure how large areas had chemicals dumped on it, and what happened after the practice became illegal.

textOriginal:
@Lucas 


Thanks for your civil reply.


"Does it pose a risk to the quality of clean air?"



No. Each cloud seeding run releases few ounces of material and is utterly insignificant, I mean non-registerable against ground level pollution. Moreover, it is very unlikely that the air that you are breathing on a daily basis is 'clean'.


"Is it a normal, organic substance in the air that we should be breathing?"


Do you drive?


"What effect do these substances have on the soil and what is the uptake into food sources?"


Zero. As I said accumulations in the soil, vegetation, and surface runoff have not been sufficiently large enough to measure above natural background levels.


"What studies have been done on the effect of these substances on the immune system of human beings?"


Toxicity is chiefly a function of time against exposure, concentration and pathway.


 "It seems so incredibly intuitive and simple, in the same way that smoking is bad for human health."


You are comparing direct inhalation of tobacco containing 4,000 chemicals and 70 known carcinogens to a few ounces of Agl dispersed into a cloud at 4,000 feet?


"People knew intuitively long before the Surgeon General put out the warning statement in 1969 about cigarettes, that they were killing people. But because studies weren't yet "conclusive" it was tolerated and ignored."


Absolutely, due to vested interests and lobbying from the highly lucrative tobacco industry. Again, you are overlooking frequency and concentration.


"I  believe that these substances have an entirely different purpose than rain........"


Then you would I think agree that several ounces would be somewhat inconsequential. 


"specifically as catalysts in the atmosphere for augmentation as well  as an inhibiting medium...."


Then you would need to demonstrate precisely how a few lbs of Agl, KI, C3H8...or dry ice has the capacity to do so. 


"I won't comment any further than that....and studies will never be done to determine their effect on the immune system."


You just did.


If cloud seeding were at all widespread or prevalent then the effects upon public health would certainly be under great scrutiny...not least for fear of legal action and litigation. Unlike smoking, establishing a causal link to the incidence of a health condition however would be virtually impossible due to the virtually negligible quantities of material employed. As I said, there are plenty of impact statements that have been undertaken, some of which have been very poorly executed and vastly over exaggerate the risks associated.


If cloud seeding were to become common practice far from the issue of the materials themselves, the main concern would be the implications of interfering with the natural equilibrium of the atmosphere. The amount of moisture in the atmosphere is determined by the balance between evaporation and precipitation. In the most unlikely scenario that cloud seeding as ever to be conducted  on a large scale, it might lead to increased evaporation from locations outside the seeding area - rain falling in one place would have fallen somewhere else. However, atmospheric budgets suggest that cloud seeding is unlikely to steal moisture from downwind sites because clouds represent a modest portion of the moisture in the atmosphere, a cloud-seeding effect of 15% would only remove about 1‚Äì2% of the total water vapour in the seeding area.

textOriginal: No, Agl is not a heavy metal (although the silver ion is). Neither are potassium iodide, dry ice or liquid propane which have also been used as cloud seeding materials. The silver constituent of Agl is merely an impurity arising from photosensitivity. Because silver iodide and not elemental silver constitutes the seeding material, the claims of damaging environmental impact have been found to be insignificant by peer-reviewed research. The negligible quantities of silver generated by cloud seeding, amount to about one percent of industry emissions into the atmosphere. Moreover, accumulations in the soil, vegetation, and surface runoff have not been sufficiently large enough to measure above natural background levels.

textOriginal: I'm not a conspiracy theorist. However, leaving stuff out in the open makes total sense for anyone who wants to get away with something. Since it causes confusion, which is a key point in deception. It goes back to that expression "you never see what's right under your nose." Divisionary tactics like this are being used right now. People in the current administration do all of these horrible things, leave it blatantly on the table for all to see, and the confusion sprung from the actions causes a huge scandal. Everyone suddenly gets caught up in emotions and wants to put a stop to the corruption, but fail to realize the event has already passed right in front of their faces while they were busy being confused. If this is repeated systemically, then eventually people become acclimated and normalize any scandalous events. So in essence you can just keep doing things and no one will ever see because their only response will be to simply try to solve the scandal, not the actual problem. In this case, if some rando world order did exist, then it would make sense that they turn people's perception into creating all sorts of conspiracy theories about them. The wilder, the better. Because it acclimates people to becoming comfortable hearing the name, and also keeps everyone's eyes away from them. If something dramatic ever does happen, then their PR can just circulate a bunch of conspiracy theories, and anyone who believes them is now labelled "crazy." Tbh this is all just basic social engineering.

*I don't remember that photograph ever being taken. I don't remember going upstairs in the house, cause that photograph is taken upstairs."
If you have never been upstairs, how do you know that that is where this photo was taken? .."The photograph is taken upstairs, and I don't think I ever went upstairs." - Fishy

videoTitle: Who Invented Nachos and Why are They Called That?
textOriginal: I heard that the fake cheese sauce is really close to plastic, like an atom off or something? Is this true?

videoTitle: Who Invented Nachos and Why are They Called That?
textOriginal:
HI!


Nachos are actually a dish similar to a traditional mexican meal, which is literally friend totilla chips slathered with every damn thing under the sun.  It is baked and the chips soak up the juices and it's served on a platter.  While I don't doubt Nacho lent his name to his snack, this mexican meal predates Nacho's nachos!

There was a special on the food network about classic mexican meals, and I'll be damned if I can find it.  :(  It was on the show that featured two mexican hosts who were immigrants and landed their own cooking show.  They went into detail about it.

textOriginal: @Hector T-- Yes, pronouncing every foreign word correctly *would* be a daunting task.  But with Spanish the rules are *easy.*  In Spanish every letter of the alphabet is *always* pronounced the same way.  There are no long or short vowels, the accent is always on the next to last syllable, unless noted by an accent mark elsewhere in the word.  It is *very* easy to learn to phonetically pronounce Spanish words and phrases.  In Simon's case, he works with native Spanish speakers on the Visual Politik channel and he could easily call someone for pronunciations.  Really, there are no excuses other than laziness or that insufferable Brittish superiority complex.

videoTitle: Who Invented Nachos and Why are They Called That?
textOriginal:
I used to try to explain the rules of phonetically pronouncing Spanish words to Simon and the crew, but it didn't do any good, AT ALL.  He works with native Spanish speakers on the Visual Politik channel and he has the ability to call and learn to pronounce the words correctly.  But he doesn't, *won't,* in fact.  It's really frustrating for Californios, like me, who grew up hearing Spanish spoken all around us, not to even mention most of our place names being Spanish.  

But you know how damn *certain* Brits are about how they are the ONLY ones who pronounce words correctly, even when it's not their native language.  They don't even acknowledge their OWN pronunciation hypocrisies.  For example: After their VAL-leT presses their tuxedo pants they take their wife to the BAL-lay.  They insist that the T in valet MUST be pronounced, unless one is IN France or another French speaking country, even though it is clearly a French word.  Yet, for no reason at all, ballet is *always* pronounced BAL-lay.  Upper class Americans (like Winchester from M*A*S*H or Frasier Crane) often do this, too.  There is a name for this upper class Euro-American accent, but I can't recall what the name is just now.  

Sometimes I think the next time I hear a Brit say TACK-o or NATCH-o I might do them an injury!

videoTitle: Who Invented Nachos and Why are They Called That?
textOriginal: Yes, there are some very small "holes" about the size of the head of a pin in natural cheddar cheese, but the giant, round, carbon dioxide holes depicted in their logo are NOT at all what cheddar looks like.  Those big air bubbles are typically only found in American Swiss, Gruyere or Emmenthaler cheeses.  The cheddaring process of stacking weights on top of the wheels of cheese as they age keeps the big air bubbles from forming in cheddar cheeses.  Therefore, the Cheddar channel's logo should NOT have holes, if they wanted to be realistic.  They could always put a cute little mouse next to the cheese to denote that it's cheese and not just a yellow block.

videoTitle: Who Invented Nachos and Why are They Called That?
textOriginal:
I've had them both ways.  When I worked at a local pizza place as a teenager in the early 80s, we'd sprinkle grated cheese on tortillas, add some jalapeno slices and toss it in the pizza oven to melt the cheese.  Later, I worked at a movie theater, where we'd squirt Rico's nacho sauce on tortilla chips and add the jalapenos to it. 

Personally, I like to add more stuff to my nachos, and I really like Taco Bueno's nacho salad, so I make my own nacho salad at home, with beans, meat, cheese (both melted and grated), lettuce and tomatoes, and maybe some sour cream on top.

videoTitle: Chemtrails
textOriginal:
It depends entirely upon the ambient atmospheric conditions. Contrails could be short lived, persistent or persistent spreading, or they may not even form at all. No different to clouds in the sky in that respect. 


Due to the fact that the atmosphere is not homogeneous or isotropic and is in continual motion, temperature, pressure and humidity - the three main factors governing contrail formation - can all vary within as little as mere metres and a matter of minutes. You can actually see visual confirmation of this frequently in the case of recently formed persistent contrails where sections of the trail will apparently randomly vanish and fade. This is due to the motion of rising or subsiding parcels of warmer/drier air. Chemtrail conspiracy theorists never mention this effect, either due to inconvenience, denial or the fact that they simply haven't noticed. 


Aircraft cruise at a range of altitudes, commonly between FL200 and FL440. It may be that contrails are not produced by one aircraft whilst another is forming lengthy persistent trails - and this may even be at a lower altitude in respect of the aircraft that isn't. Also, this may be within as little as 1,000 feet of vertical separation which in the lower stratosphere is impossible to discern as a ground based observer.

videoTitle: Chemtrails
textOriginal:
No - atmospheric conditions. 


 A contrail is merely a form of artificially induced cirrus. The governing factors are temperature, humidity and pressure. A contrail may be short lived, persistent of persistent spreading - or it may not form at all. In the regions that commercial aircraft cruise - the tropopause and lower stratosphere - the ambient air is frequently saturated in respect to ice. In cases of high RHi then a contrail will persist because the ice crystals are unable to sublimate back into the invisible gaseous phase (water vapour). However is cases of ice supersaturation, the water present in aircraft exhaust merely initiates the contrail. The growth comes from the available atmospheric moisture budget, which is precisely why a contrail can weigh millions of tonnes. It is also the reason that it can spread, thicken and become indistinguishable from regular cirrus. 


The science of contrail cirrus is explained here:


https://journals.ametsoc.org/doi/full/10.1175/1520-0469%282000%29057%3C0464%3AOTTOCI%3E2.0.CO%3B2


You may also wish to read this...


https://www.atmos-chem-phys.net/9/6229/2009/acp-9-6229-2009.pdf
